  <h2 id="opportunity-attributes-1" class="govuk-heading-m app-summary-list-heading">Overview</h2>
  
  

  

  

  

  

  

  

  
<dl class="govuk-summary-list app-govuk-summary-list app-govuk-summary-list--top-border govuk-!-margin-bottom-8">
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          Off-payroll (IR35) determination
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          Contracted out service: the off-payroll rules do not apply
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          Summary of the work
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          DCMS are seeking a supplier team to lead on an outcome-based contract to provide the necessary knowledge, skills and experience to lead a process of discovery, development and delivery for a prototype technological solution designed to address barriers of cross-Whitehall working and create a commonly understood information picture of disinformation.
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          Latest start date
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          Monday 18 October 2021
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          Expected contract length
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          18 months,  optional 3 months extension. Option for Customer to terminate after phase 1
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          Location
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          No specific location, for example they can work remotely
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          Organisation the work is for
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          Budget range
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          Total project estimated cost of £1,500,000 to £2,000,000 (for the complete project). <br>DCMS anticipates that the Discovery phase (Phase 1) should cost no more than £300k - £400k.
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
</dl>

  <h2 id="opportunity-attributes-2" class="govuk-heading-m app-summary-list-heading">About the work</h2>
  
  

  

  

  

  

  

  

  
<dl class="govuk-summary-list app-govuk-summary-list app-govuk-summary-list--top-border govuk-!-margin-bottom-8">
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          Why the work is being done
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          Disinformation is a multifaceted issue which requires a number of areas of cross-government expertise and, as a result, monitoring, analysis and policy functions are spread across a number of departments and agencies. Whilst DCMS provides coordination of these efforts, there exist several significant limitations to more effective use of data, with enhanced capability increasingly needed to produce a comprehensive picture of disinformation and to support our response to the growing threat that it poses. <br><br>DCMS has been successful in securing funding to deliver the Counter-Disinformation Data Platform project. The overarching objective of this pilot project is to improve HMG’s counter-disinformation capability: developing a more accurate, detailed and targeted understanding how harmful narratives are emerging and evolving over time, improving counter-disinformation data sharing across relevant government stakeholders, limiting duplication of effort and enabling effective interventions which reduce harm. We are looking for a multi-disciplinary supplier team to partner with to provide the necessary knowledge, skills and experience to lead a process of discovery, development and delivery for a prototype technological solution designed to address barriers and create a commonly understood information picture of disinformation.
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          Problem to be solved
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          We are seeking a supplier team to help us to develop and deliver a digital solution designed to ingest and store anonymised social media data, to allow for large scale analysis of narrative trends to understand how these are evolving over time. This solution will identify key areas of risk and help HMG to address the evolving and sophisticated tactics used by malign actors, with an overall goal of mitigating the negative impacts of mis/disinformation and reducing harm. <br><br>The contracted project team will be involved across two phases of the project and will be responsible for delivering the outcome. To achieve this, the team will be expected to lead a Discovery process in Phase 1 (3 months), exploring and testing innovative ways of addressing barriers, understanding users needs and working through a range of questions which will need to be answered to ensure the feasibility of the project. The team will then project manage the development and the process of the technical build in Phase 2 through the Delivery phase (lasting approximately 12-14 months) informing the design of the solution. The discovery phase must be completed by January 2022 and the solution must be in place by March 2023.
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          Who the users are and what they need to do
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          Users will be internal teams across government. Primary users of the solution will be a team of analysts, who will use the anonymised social media data to produce insight to inform policymakers.<br><br>Analysts <br>Analysts will need to have access to anonymised social media data and analytical tools at an appropriate level, including accessing data which is held outside individual departments to generate high quality insights to inform policy making and delivery. Analysts will be based in teams across Government and will use the platform to connect, collaborate and share with other users across departmental boundaries and silos.<br><br>Policymakers<br>Policymakers need a whole-of-government, shared understanding of disinformation and an enhanced approach to developing and delivering government interventions, informed by data and using all available tools.
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          Early market engagement
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          Prior to this tender we took part in an early-market engagement exercise. We shared our initial specification and invited four suppliers to discuss the most appropriate delivery route. We also encouraged suppliers to comment on our strategic approach to procurement and our specification of requirements. <br>The results of engagement have informed the requirements, with the key changes in approach being that the team who will deliver the technical build will be procured separately, potentially prior to the beginning of Phase 2, to allow for the findings of Discovery to shape the requirements.
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          Any work that’s already been done
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          We have had initial contact with other key government stakeholders who are likely to be users of the platform, to confirm their support for the project. No further work has been conducted and there is no incumbent.
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          Existing team
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          The supplier will work alongside the DCMS Counter Disinformation Data Platform internal project management team of three. This team’s responsibilities include administering contracts, providing secretariat for project delivery meetings and governance and leading cross-Government engagement. The project will also be supported by five project-specific analysts. Other relevant government departments will also be providing support and input on the content and format.<br><br>The supplier will not be expected to deliver the technical build of the solution, in Phase 2 but will project manage this process and will work alongside and interact with the contracted team as required.
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          Current phase
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          Not started
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
</dl>

  <h2 id="opportunity-attributes-3" class="govuk-heading-m app-summary-list-heading">Work setup</h2>
  
  

  

  

  
<dl class="govuk-summary-list app-govuk-summary-list app-govuk-summary-list--top-border govuk-!-margin-bottom-8">
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          Address where the work will take place
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          Due to COVID-19 restrictions, we expect the supplier will conduct the majority of their work remotely in the UK, however, as restrictions ease there may be a requirement for entry to the London Office (100 Parliament Street, London SW1A 2BQ) for face to face meetings.
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          Working arrangements
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          The Supplier will be expected to work off-site using their own devices. <br><br>Throughout the duration of the project we expect:<br>Weekly check-in video calls with the internal project team;<br>Monthly updates on progress remotely/ over video call while restrictions are in place and potentially in person when it becomes safe to do so;<br>Ad-hoc calls/meetings as needed by default video calls but if necessary these may happen in person if it is in line with government guidance.<br>All expenses must be included within the supplier&#39;s fee.
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          Security clearance
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          All supplier personnel involved in this project should have a valid Baseline Personnel Security Standard (BPSS) clearance as minimum prior to starting work. Security Check (SC) clearance will be necessary for at least one member of the team.
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
</dl>

  <h2 id="opportunity-attributes-4" class="govuk-heading-m app-summary-list-heading">Additional information</h2>
  
  

  
<dl class="govuk-summary-list app-govuk-summary-list app-govuk-summary-list--top-border govuk-!-margin-bottom-8">
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          Additional terms and conditions
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          The standard contract will be used. <br>Note that the contract will have a break clause at the end of Phase 1 (est. December 2021) with the customer retaining the right to terminate the contract following Discovery. One of the outputs from Discovery will be a review detailing the feasibility of the project, providing assurances that the proposed approach is viable and will work. Funding for subsequent phases of the work will be dependent on an assessment of this review by HM Treasury officials.
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
</dl>

  <h2 id="opportunity-attributes-5" class="govuk-heading-m app-summary-list-heading">Skills and experience</h2>
  
  <p class="govuk-body govuk-!-margin-top-3">Buyers will use the essential and nice-to-have skills and experience to help them evaluate suppliers’ technical competence.</p>
  
  

  

  
<dl class="govuk-summary-list app-govuk-summary-list app-govuk-summary-list--top-border govuk-!-margin-bottom-8">
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          Essential skills and experience
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
          <li>Have demonstrable experience of digital/ technical project management, taking an agile approach to the design and delivery of services</li>
          <li>Have demonstrable experience in conducting Discovery and applying the principles of user centred design to the development of digital solutions</li>
          <li>Have demonstrable experience in leading a project through Alpha and Beta stages of technical delivery to deliver a prototype digital solution</li>
          <li>Have the ability to assess the benefits and risks of options and make recommendations as to which are most appropriate to explore further</li>
          <li>Have the ability to assess and identify the significance of existing barriers around data sharing</li>
          <li>Have demonstrable experience designing data structures and creating solutions which take into account legal, practical and ethical barriers and concerns</li>
          <li>Have demonstrable experience of leading and coordinating multidisciplinary/multi-organisation teams</li>
          <li>Have demonstrable experience of developing work requiring data &amp; process to be handled with elevated security measures</li>
          <li>Have demonstrable experience working to the GDS Service Standard, including the Service Design Manual, Technology Code of Practice and wider industry standards</li>
          <li>Have demonstrable experience of delivering solutions that fulfil WCAG 2.1 standards</li>
        </ul>
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          Nice-to-have skills and experience
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
          <li>Demonstrate experience of working on digital projects for organisations of a similar size and complexity</li>
          <li>Demonstrate experience of developing strategies for better use of data across organisations/departments</li>
          <li>Demonstrate experience of designing collaborative services for use by multiple organisations/departments</li>
          <li>Demonstrate experience working with secure data in similar environments</li>
          <li>Provide evidence of strong knowledge of government and industry data security legislation, policy, patterns, standards</li>
          <li>Provide evidence of strong knowledge/ experience of working on projects relating to/understanding of safety tech, disinformation and related risks to the information environment</li>
        </ul>
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
</dl>

  <h2 id="opportunity-attributes-6" class="govuk-heading-m app-summary-list-heading">How suppliers will be evaluated</h2>
  
  <p class="govuk-body govuk-!-margin-top-3">All suppliers will be asked to provide a written proposal.</p>
  
  

  

  

  

  

  

  
<dl class="govuk-summary-list app-govuk-summary-list app-govuk-summary-list--top-border govuk-!-margin-bottom-8">
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          How many suppliers to evaluate
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          5
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          Proposal criteria
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
          <li>Conflict of Interest (Pass/Fail)</li>
          <li>Cyber essentials/ Cyber essentials plus ISO27001 (Pass/Fail)</li>
          <li>Understanding of Project Objectives - 10%</li>
          <li>Proposed Approach and Methodology - 15%</li>
          <li>How the approach aligns with the Cabinet Office’s service standard delivery methodology - 5%</li>
          <li>Skills, Expertise and Capacity - 10%</li>
          <li>Understanding of the Sector - 10%</li>
          <li>Project Management and Delivery - 10%</li>
          <li>Case Study - 5%</li>
        </ul>
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          Cultural fit criteria
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
          <li>Work collaboratively as a team with our organisation and with other suppliers, being comfortable making recommendations to non-technical audiences - 3%</li>
          <li>Have a committed, proactive and ethical approach to work - 5%</li>
          <li>Have experience of working with organisations of a similar size and complexity and with a range of different stakeholders - 2%</li>
        </ul>
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          Payment approach
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          Fixed price
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          Additional assessment methods
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          Case study
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
