        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          14. The Authority has asked, “Demonstrate experience of working on digital projects for organisations of a similar size and complexity.” Is the Authority able to share any volumetrics to inform this response, i.e. data volumes, End Users, transactions per second, number of interfaces, etc?
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          We do not have volumetric data to inform the response as we anticipate that these issues will be scoped as part of the discovery work. For this criteria we are looking for evidence of experience of working with organisations with a range of competing stakeholder needs and motivations, which may have a complex organisational structure
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          15. Can you explain what is meant by “Experience of tailoring delivery approaches in line with performance” – are you looking to tie payment to delivery performance, or do you mean something else?
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          By tailoring, we mean the supplier would have experience in managing flexible and agile projects and revisiting their approach if needed due to changing dependencies. <br>The use of ‘performance’ refers to the expected progress against agreed planned activities for both client &amp; supplier.
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
