        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          The proposed makeup of the team is one of the selection criteria and so we are looking for suppliers to propose the size and make up of the team you deem to be appropriate against the requirement.
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          21. Please can you confirm if being chosen as the successful supplier for the Project Management Team will preclude that supplier from any future procurement concerning the technical build in Phase 2?
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          The successful supplier will have the opportunity to bid for the delivery of the build contract. This will be tendered through a separate process.
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          22. As Cyber Essentials and ISO27001 are different, please can you confirm whether you require Cyber essentials/Cyber essentials Plus Certification AND ISO27001 accreditation, or whether this is an either/or requirement?
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          We would expect suppliers to have certification of either Cyber Essentials or Cyber Essentials plus, as well as ISO27001. Lack of ISO27001 certification would be a fail against the proposed criteria.
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          23. Are you content for bidders to use private sector examples for the Essential and Nice to Have skills and experience providing the example provided is relevant to the question posed? We believe our private sector experience will be valuable in the context of some of the questions posed.
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          Yes, we are content for suppliers to use private sector examples where relevant. We are looking for suppliers to demonstrate that they have the Essential and Nice-to-have Skills and Experience when responding to the questions, and we will consider any relevant experience that allows them to demonstrate this.
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          24. Do you anticipate there will be a gap between Discovery and Build (phase 2)?
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          In our current draft timelines, the Discovery Phase (Phase 1) is expected to last 3 months between October and December 2021. The Delivery Phase (Phase 2) is then expected to start in January 2022, so we do not anticipate a large gap between the phases, though there will be a short review period to ensure feasibility of the second phase. <br><br>Note that timelines may be subject to change
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          25. For question “Provide evidence of strong knowledge/ experience of working on projects relating to/understanding of safety tech, disinformation and related risks to the information environment” please could you elaborate on what you are looking for in terms of “safety tech” in the context of this project?
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          Safety tech refers to the development of technology or solutions to facilitate safer online experiences, and to protect users from harmful content, contact or conduct. We are looking for suppliers to provide evidence of experience or understanding  ways in which technology or solutions can be applied to the challenge of identifying and responding to mis/disinformation or related harms.
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          26. In a previous question you stated ‘Lack of ISO27001 certification would be a fail against the proposed criteria.’ If a supplier were currently going through the process of accreditation and could demonstrate a plan of how they were going to achieve ISO accreditation by a certain date, would this meet the pass criteria?
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          Where ISO accreditation does not exist potential suppliers must demonstrate as part of their response at what stage they are in the accreditation process. They should provide indicative timeframes on when they expect to receive this by and the organisation undertaking the assessment. Ideally this should be in place at the point of contract award for assurance purposes and is a mandated requirement.
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          27. Considering your statement “The results of engagement have informed the requirements, with the key changes in approach being that the team who will deliver the technical build will be procured separately, potentially prior to the beginning of Phase 2, to allow for the findings of Discovery to shape the requirements.”, are there any other reasons why the procurement is being split?
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          Procurement is being split as the contract includes a break clause scheduled at the end of Phase 1, in December 2021. The continuation of the project is subject to HMT releasing the funding for Phase 2 following the submission of a review detailing the feasibility of the project, and providing assurances that the proposed approach will work after the end of the planned discovery work.<br><br>The break clause allows us to terminate the contract in the unlikely event that we are unable to proceed with the project, or if the supplier is not adequately meeting the needs of the contract.
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          28. With regards to IP, if a supplier were to invest its own funding in the development of the deliverable, therefore reducing the costs significantly, would you consider providing perpetual royalty free rights to use the research outcome for the purposes of developing a product independently of the customer?
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          We would not be able to facilitate this, though we may explore options to provide wider access to the solution as part of the project.
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          29. To provide a little wider context, please could you share some examples of the sort of disinformation that would be relevant here?
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          HMG defines Disinformation as the deliberate creation and dissemination of false and/or manipulated information that is intended to deceive and mislead audiences, either for the purposes of causing harm, or for political, personal or financial gain.
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          30. Can you confirm whether or not the complete budget for this work also includes a future build project?
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          If yes, can you please give an indication of what proportion of that complete budget you expect to make available for this work?
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          31. Can you confirm whether or not the complete budget for this work also includes a future build project?<br>If yes, can you please give an indication of what proportion of that complete budget you expect to make available for this work?
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          DCMS anticipate that the total estimated cost of the Project Management Team will be between £1,500,000 and £2,000,000 for the entire process (both ‘discovery’ in Phase 1, and ‘delivery’ in Phase 2). <br><br>There is a separate budget for the supplier team who will be procured before delivery in Phase 2 to build the solution.
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          32. Could you clarify the precise contractual delivery responsibilities for the supplier team in P2 as it is unclear whether the scope is to lead delivery, take responsibility for the outcome or project manage another unspecified supplier’s delivery. The documentation states:<br>“seeking a supplier team to…lead a process of discovery, development and delivery for a prototype.”<br>“supplier team will be responsible for delivering the outcome.”<br>“team will then project manage the development and the process of the technical build in P2”<br>“supplier will not be expected to deliver the technical build of the solution...but will project manage”
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          In ‘discovery’ in Phase 1, the Project Team will define the technical build team requirements.<br><br>In the ‘delivery’ in Phase 2, the Project Team will be augmented by the procurement of additional specialists who will inform the design and the development of the data platform project, and will be contracted to build the solution itself. <br><br>In Phase 2, the Project Team will manage project development and the process of the technical build of the solution, ensuring that adequate protections are in place for freedom of expression and privacy and providing sufficient protections to keep data anonymised, with regular stakeholder testing.
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          33. What proportion of the total project estimated cost of £1,500,000 to £2,000,000 is ring-fenced for the supplier who will deliver the technical build of the solution, and what portion is allocated to this project management task?
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          DCMS anticipate that the total estimated cost of the Project Management Team will be between £1,500,000 and £2,000,000 for the entire process (both ‘discovery’ in Phase 1, and ‘delivery’ in Phase 2). <br><br>There is a separate budget for the supplier team who will be procured before delivery in Phase 2 to build the solution
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          34. Why is the digital solution required to ingest and store only social media data that is anonymised?
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          To ensure that adequate protections are in place for freedom of expression and privacy, it will be important that the data is anonymised.
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          35. What is the required ‘Technology Readiness Level’ (TRL) of the ‘prototype technological solution’ on delivery of the solution in March 2023 (<a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/news/guidance-on-technology-readiness-levels" class="govuk-link" rel="external">https://www.gov.uk/government/news/guidance-on-technology-readiness-levels</a>)
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          Answering these questions ahead of the discovery phase would be premature.<br><br>The Project Team is expected to use the agile approach to project management to build and run the service. Agile methods encourage teams to build quickly, test what they’ve built and iterate their work based on regular feedback. As such, where applicable, this agile approach will inform the TRL throughout the discovery and delivery phases.
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          36. What is the expected scope of supplier responsibility for both business design and technical design under this contract? It is unclear whether design responsibility rests with this team, or the supplier who will deliver the technical build of the solution; or whether the technical build supplier is responsible for both technical and business design. The tender states:<br>• “the solution must be in place by March 2023”.<br>• “The team will then project manage the development and the process of the technical build … informing the design of the solution”
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          In ‘discovery’ in Phase 1, the Project Team will define the technical build team requirements.<br><br>In the ‘delivery’ in Phase 2, the Project Team will be augmented by the procurement of additional specialists who will inform the design and the development of the data platform project, and will be contracted to build the solution itself. <br><br>In Phase 2, the Project Team will manage project development and the process of the technical build of the solution, ensuring that adequate protections are in place for freedom of expression and privacy and providing sufficient protections to keep data anonymised, with regular stakeholder testing.
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          37. In what capacity are you expecting the contracted team to participate in the procurement for the team who will deliver the technical build?
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          The successful supplier of this procurement will be the project team to lead the process of ‘discovery’ in Phase 1. In this phase, the project team will help to define the technical build team requirements and contribute to the procurement of the team who will deliver the technical build in the ‘delivery’ in Phase 2.<br><br>The team who will deliver the technical build will be tendered through the Digital Marketplace in a separate process.
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
</dl>



  </div>
</div>





        </main>
      </div>
    

    
